Document: SkeletonIK3D
Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonik3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the SkeletonIK3D node, which controls inverse kinematics for 3D skeletons.

Property: interpolation (float)
Method: set_interpolation(value: float)
Method: get_interpolation() -> float
Deprecated: Use SkeletonModifier3D.influence instead.
Interpolation value for how much the IK results are applied to the current skeleton bone chain. A value of 1.0 will overwrite all skeleton bone transforms completely while a value of 0.0 will visually disable the SkeletonIK.

Property: magnet (Vector3)
Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0)
Method: set_magnet_position(value: Vector3)
Method: get_magnet_position() -> Vector3
Secondary target position (first is target property or target_node) for the IK chain. Use magnet position (pole target) to control the bending of the IK chain. Only works if the bone chain has more than 2 bones. The middle chain bone position will be linearly interpolated with the magnet position.

Property: max_iterations (int)
Default: 10
Method: set_max_iterations(value: int)
Method: get_max_iterations() -> int
Number of iteration loops used by the IK solver to produce more accurate (and elegant) bone chain results.

Property: min_distance (float)
Default: 0.01
Method: set_min_distance(value: float)
Method: get_min_distance() -> float
The minimum distance between bone and goal target. If the distance is below this value, the IK solver stops further iterations.

Property: override_tip_basis (bool)
Default: true
Method: set_override_tip_basis(value: bool)
Method: is_override_tip_basis() -> bool
If true overwrites the rotation of the tip bone with the rotation of the target (or target_node if defined).

Property: root_bone (StringName)
Default: ""
Method: set_root_bone(value: StringName)
Method: get_root_bone() -> StringName
The name of the current root bone, the first bone in the IK chain.

Property: target (Transform3D)
Default: Transform3D(1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0)
Method: set_target_transform(value: Transform3D)
Method: get_target_transform() -> Transform3D
First target of the IK chain where the tip bone is placed and, if override_tip_basis is true, how the tip bone is rotated. If a target_node path is available the nodes transform is used instead and this property is ignored.

Property: target_node (NodePath)
Default: NodePath("")
Method: set_target_node(value: NodePath)
Method: get_target_node() -> NodePath
Target node NodePath for the IK chain. If available, the node's current Transform3D is used instead of the target property.

Property: tip_bone (StringName)
Default: ""
Method: set_tip_bone(value: StringName)
Method: get_tip_bone() -> StringName
The name of the current tip bone, the last bone in the IK chain placed at the target transform (or target_node if defined).

Property: use_magnet (bool)
Default: false
Method: set_use_magnet(value: bool)
Method: is_using_magnet() -> bool
If true, instructs the IK solver to consider the secondary magnet target (pole target) when calculating the bone chain. Use the magnet position (pole target) to control the bending of the IK chain.
